Sentencas: PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+delta (PBCNO)-xCe(0.8)Sm(0.2)O(1.9) (SDC) (x = 0, 10, 20,30, 40, and 50 wt%) composites are investigated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD results show that PBCNO is chemically compatible with the SDC electrolyte at 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The thermal expansion coefficient (TEC) decreases with the increase of SDC content.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average TEC at the temperature range of 35-900 degrees C decreases from 22.6 x 10(-6) K-1 for pure PBCNO cathode to 15.2 x 10(-6)K(-1) for PBCNO-50SDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The addition of SDC reduces the polarization resistance.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The lowest polarization resistance of 0.012 Omega cm(2) is achieved at 800 degrees C for the PBCNO-40SDC composite cathode.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In the temperature range of 600-800 degrees C, the PBCNO-40SDC composite cathode delivers the power density of 483 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C. These results indicate that PBCNO-40SDC is a promising cathode material for TT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Preparation and characterization of PrBaCo1.9Ni0.1O5+δ-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9 composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
